| Lines 665-673 | **keydown D**: Instead of calling `stripAllOverrides()` immediately, schedules it via `setTimeout(вҖҰ, 150)`. Timer ref stored for cancellation |
| Lines 703-715 | **keyup D**: If timer is still pending (`diffTimerRef.current !== null`), cancels it via `clearTimeout` вҖ” no visual change occurs. If timer already fired, restores overrides normally |
| Lines 1007-1010 | **cleanup effect**: Clears pending timer on unmount to prevent leaked timeouts |

